sql:
SELECT source_id
FROM news_sources
WHERE source_id BETWEEN 1 AND 100 AND name <> 'BBC';

SELECT name
FROM news_sources
ORDER BY name ASC;

external_knowledge:
- Sentiment score > 0.7 indicates the article has a very positive tone;
- Comment score > 4.7 suggests comments are highly favorable or enthusiastic;
- 'Upbeat news outlets' refers to sources with a high sentiment score in their articles;
- 'Enthusiastic reactions' refer to high comment scores given by the users.

sql:
SELECT articles.title
FROM articles
INNER JOIN fake_news_reports ON articles.article_id = fake_news_reports.article_id;

external_knowledge:
- Recently published articles are those published within the last month;
- Popular articles in this context are those associated with a variety of labels, indicating they cover a broad range of topics;
- The variety of labels refers to unique tags, with more than five different tags indicating diverse content.

sql:
SELECT title, sentiment_score
FROM articles
WHERE sentiment_score > (SELECT AVG(sentiment_score) FROM articles);

external_knowledge:
